text: Tenille Dashwood (born 1 March 1989) is an Australian professional wrestler. She is best known for her time in WWE from 2011–2017 under the ring name Emma. In 2018, Dashwood began working for Ring of Honor, Impact Wrestling and several more promotions under her real name. She returned to WWE in 2022 but was released again in 2023. Before WWE, she used the ring name Tenille Tayla. Dashwood was born in Boronia, a suburb of Melbourne, Victoria. She lives in Orlando, Florida, United States. ==Personal life== On 30 June 2014, before Monday Night Raw aired, Dashwood was arrested in Hartford, in the U.S. state of Connecticut for sixth-degree larceny. Dashwood's lawyer said that she had forgotten to pay for an iPad case, when she was using the self-checkout machine at a Walmart. After she appeared at a community court on 1 July, she was ordered to do one day of community service and complete an online course. On 2 July 2014, Emma was released by WWE after she was arrested for sixth- degree larceny. She was reinstated by WWE two hours later. On August 4, 2022, Dashwood revealed that she is dating Michael Rallis, who is best known by his ring name Riddick Moss. On June 3, 2023, Dashwood and Rallis announced their engagement. The couple married March 8, 2024. On September 6, 2024, Dashwood announced that she is expecting her first child with Rallis in 2025. On March 4, 2025, Dashwood gave birth to their first son. ==Championships== America World Wrestling * AWW Women's World Championship (1 time) * Extreme Canadian Championship Wrestling ** ECCW Supergirls Championship (2 times) * Impact Wrestling ** Impact Knockouts World Tag Team Championship (1 time) – with Madison Rayne * Pro Wrestling Alliance Queensland ** Queen of the Warriors (2009) * Pro Wrestling Illustrated ** Ranked No. 31 of the top 50 female wrestlers in the PWI Female 50 in 2015 * Slam Wrestling Awards ** Worst Tag Team Female (2021) – with Madison Rayne * Swiss Wrestling Entertainment ** SWE Ladies Championship (1 time) * Women's Wrestling Fan Awards ** Best Independent Wrestler of the Year (2018) ==References== ==Other websites== *Official website * Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Australian models Category:Australian professional wrestlers Category:Female professional wrestlers Category:Former WWE wrestlers Category:Professional wrestling managers and valets Category:Sportspeople from Melbourne Category:Total Nonstop Action Wrestling alumni
